America. Note that none of the proper nouns has an article before it. Articles, however,

36
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:36,680
must remain in place if they are part of the full name of something, like the newspaper,

37
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:44,040
the New York Times, musical group, A Tribe Called Quest, and country, the Netherlands.

38
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:52,120
Here's an example. My favorite musical group in high school was A Tribe Called Quest.

39
00:05:53,100 --> 00:06:02,220
Now on to transport phrases. No article is used with some phrases that relate to transportation,

40
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:12,900
such as by car, by train, by bus, by air, and on foot. Take this example.

41
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:18,880
The group traveled from Tangier to Casablanca by train.

42
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:28,160
In addition, we do not use articles with some time words and phrases such as at night,

43
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:40,480
at midnight, tomorrow, today, and yesterday. Articles also are not used for general time phrases

44
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:51,340
beginning with the word last, such as last night, last week, and last year, as in this example.

45
00:06:52,920 --> 00:07:00,440
Last week, I took a painting class for the first time. Next, no article is used

46
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:08,620
for some phrases that relate to well-known institutions or places, such as at home,

47
00:07:09,060 --> 00:07:17,980
at work, at school, in class, in college, and in jail. Take this example.

48
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:23,540
Sorry, I can't talk right now. I'm at work. I'll call you later.

49
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:31,620
However, in American English, there are a few exceptions, such as at the hospital.

50
